quran[50]{c,v,t}:
  15,50,And that My doom is a grievous doom
  15,51,And inform them concerning Abraham´s guests
  15,52,"When they came unto him and said, \"Peace!\", he said, \"Verily, we are afraid of you"
  15,53,"They said, \"Be not afraid! Verily, we bring you glad tidings of a boy possessing wisdom"
  15,54,"He said, \"Do you bring me this glad tidings when old age has overtaken me? Of what then do you bring good tidings"
  15,55,"They said, \"We bring you glad tidings in truth, then be not of those who despair"
  15,56,"He said, \"Who would despair of the mercy of his Lord save those who err"
  15,57,"He said, \"What then is your business, O you messengers"
  15,58,"They said, \"Verily, we are sent unto a people deeply in guilt"
  15,59,"Save only the household (family or adherents) of Lot, all of them we are certainly charged to save"
  15,60,"Except his wife, of whom we have ascertained that she shall be of those who stay behind"
  15,61,And when the messengers came unto the adherents of Lot
  15,62,"He said, \"Verily, you are a people whom I recognize not (or of uncommon appearance)"
  15,63,"They said, \"Yea, we have come to you to accomplish that whereof they keep disputing"
  15,64,"And we bring you the truth (or the inevitable), and, verily, we are truth-tellers"
  15,65,"Travel then with your household in the deep darkness of the night, and follow you their rear; and let not any one of you turn round to look back; but go on to where you are commanded"
  15,66,And We made plain for him the decree that the uttermost one of these people should be cut off on the morrow
  15,67,"Then the people of the city came, glad at the tidings (of the arrival of the young men)"
  15,68,"Said Lot, \"Verily, these are my guests, therefore disgrace me not"
  15,69,"But fear Allah, and put me not to shame"
  15,70,"They said, \"Have we not forbidden you to speak for all in the world"
  15,71,"He said, \"Here are my daughters, if do it you must"
  15,72,By your life (O Muhammad)! In their frenzy of intoxication (passion) they went blindly (distractedly) to and fro
  15,73,And the mighty blast caught them at dawn
  15,74,"And We turned their cities upside down, and rained down on them brimstones hard as baked clay"
  15,75,Behold! In this is a sign to those who by tokens understand (or can read the signs)
  15,76,"And, verily, the cities were on a high road that still remains"
  15,77,"Verily, in this is a sign for those who believe"
  15,78,"And the companions of the Wood (Midian), too, were unjust"
  15,79,"And We took vengeance on them, and, verily, they were both on an open highway, plain to see"
  15,80,And the companions of Al-Hijr (the Rocky Tract) also rejected the messengers
  15,81,"And We brought them Our revelations, but they did turn away there from"
  15,82,And they used to hew out dwellings from the mountain to dwell in safety
  15,83,But the mighty blast seized them in the morning
  15,84,And that which they counted as gain availed them naught
  15,85,"We created not the heavens and the earth and all that is between them both, save with truth. And, verily, the Hour is surely coming; then do you forgive with a gracious forgiveness"
  15,86,"Verily, your Lord He is the Master Creator, the All-knowing"
  15,87,"We have already given you the Seven Oft-Repeated (the verses of the first chapter of the Quran), and the mighty Quran"
  15,88,"Let not your eyes strain after what We have allowed certain classes among them to enjoy, nor grieve for them; but lower your wing (in tenderness) to the believers"
  15,89,"And say, \"Verily, I, even I, am a plain Warner"
  15,90,Such as We sent down for those who make divisions
  15,91,Those who break the Quran into separate parts
  15,92,"Them, by your Lord! We shall question, one and all"
  15,93,About what they used to do
  15,94,"Therefore, proclaim what you are commanded, and withdraw from the idolaters"
  15,95,"Verily, We are enough defence for you against the scoffers"
  15,96,Who place other gods along with Allah; but they at length shall come to know
  15,97,And well know We that your breast was at times oppressed by what they say
  15,98,"But hymn the praises of your Lord, and be you of those who make prostrations (or obeisance)"
  15,99,And serve your Lord until there comes unto you the Hour that is certain (death)